snippet.textDisplay:
Punjabi language songs nearly out number Urdu language songs in this season. I love Punjabi, but I was wondering if Pakistani music is all that is in Urdu and Punjabi? I can understand that Urdu is national language, so fine. but why much emphasis on Punjabi language songs? I mean take this song..there was really no need to include it in this episode/season. you have to balance and keep it versatile. I mean Balochi, Pashto, Sindhi languages have great folk music which could be included in this season instead of this crap. I miss Rohail Hayat. he was versatile. He brought gems from folk music of different languages and dialects which we enjoyed most, though never understood a word of them. 
is this because strings guys and other musicians in this season are mainly from Punjab? They don't want to work hard and explore Pakistan's greatest musical traditions? correct me if I'm wrong!
